NAME: APPLICATION
DESCRIPTION: Flag for type of application being modeled

DESCRIPTION: Flag for type of process being modeled

NAME: SUBPROCESS
DESCRIPTION: Flag for type of subprocess being modeled

NAME: ALPHA
DESCRIPTION: Controls weighting of upstream values in advection approximations when :envvar:`IORDER` = 1

NAME: ALPHA_SWAT
DESCRIPTION: Controls weighting of upstream values in advection approximations in the shallow water model when :envvar:`IORDER_SWAT` = 1

NAME: DTIMPX
DESCRIPTION: Maximum Courant number used to limit the time step size in the implicit advection model, :envvar:`IMPADV` = 1. Used in addition to any other limiting factors.

NAME: IFENRG
DESCRIPTION: Flag for internal energy evaluation

NAME: IFPK
DESCRIPTION: Flag for F-packing

NAME: IFRHO
DESCRIPTION: Flag for density evaluation

NAME: IFTHEXP
DESCRIPTION: Thermal expansion flag for flow with density a function of temperature

NAME: IFVOF
DESCRIPTION: Flag for F advection options

NAME: IFSLP
DESCRIPTION: Flag for two-fluid interface velocity slip option

NAME: IMPADV
DESCRIPTION: Advection explicit/implicit flag

NAME: IMPADV2
DESCRIPTION: Time step control flag for implicit advection option, :envvar:`IMPADV` = 1

NAME: IORDER

NAME: IBM

NAME: IBM_PROBE_DIRECTION_METHOD

NAME: DT_THRESH
DESCRIPTION: Time step threshold for implicit advection. Cells with local advective stability limit below :envvar:`DT_THRESH` are treated implicitly. Used when :envvar:`IMPADV` = 1 and :envvar:`IMPADV2` = 2.

NAME: V_THRESH
DESCRIPTION: Velocity threshold for implicit advection. Cells with velocity above :envvar:`V_THRESH` are treated implicitly. Used when :envvar:`IMPADV` = 1 and :envvar:`IMPADV2` = 1.

NAME: IF_VOL_CORR
DESCRIPTION: Flag for fluid #1 volume correction model. Only applied to one-fluid with free-surface and two-fluid problems to maintain fluid #1 volume conservation.

NAME: IVOL_CORR_TIME
DESCRIPTION: Flag for the definition of the characteristic time for volume correction :envvar:`VOL_CORR_TIME`

NAME: VOL_CORR_TIME
DESCRIPTION: Characteristic time for fluid #1 volume correction. Defaults to 10.0 when :envvar:`IVOL_CORR_TIME` = 1. Must be positive when :envvar:`IVOL_CORR_TIME` = 2.

NAME: ICLID
DESCRIPTION: Flag for the collision model. Only applied to the coupled-motion GMO components

NAME: FRCMOB
DESCRIPTION: Global coefficient of friction during collision between coupled-motion GMO components and other components and walls

NAME: STRNGMOB
DESCRIPTION: Global coefficient of Stronge's restitution during collision between coupled-motion GMO components and other components and walls. Values should be between 0.0 and 1.0.

NAME: ITETTSE
DESCRIPTION: Flag to use tetrahedral meshing to generate the mesh of the solidified fluid region of the thermal stress evolution model. Default is hexahedral meshes, and this value is overridden when reading in an existing mesh from a file (see :envvar:`IFFEMF` in :ref:`namelistXPUTFileControlOptions`).

NAME: ICPLTSE
DESCRIPTION: Flag to control coupling between the solidified fluid region (the Thermal Stress Evolution region) and neighboring Fluid Structure Interaction (FSI) components (see :envvar:`IFSI(m)` in :ref:`ComponentPropertiesFluidStructureInteractionFSImodel`). Default is only basic constraining/non-constraining behavior between the TSE region and neighboring FSI components (see :envvar:`IFSOFT(m)` in :ref:`ComponentPropertiesThermalStressEvolutionTSEModel`).

NAME: FRCTTSE
DESCRIPTION: Friction coefficient between Thermal Stress Evolution (TSE) region and neighboring Fluid Structure Interaction (FSI) components. A negative value indicates that the coefficient is infinite (i.e., tangential traction is not limited), and a positive value indicates the friction coefficient. Its value represents the ratio between the limit of the magnitude of tangential traction to the normal traction between the TSE region and the component face. Physical values are typically less than 1.0.

NAME: IGMRES
DESCRIPTION: Pressure iteration option

NAME: IOPT_GMRES
DESCRIPTION: Convergence criterion for the GMRES pressure solver. The GMRES pressure solver uses two types of convergence criteria. The absolute convergence criterion (v11.1 and earlier) uses a simple absolute convergence limit for the residual. The hybrid convergence criterion (v11.2 and later) uses a combination of absolute and relative convergence limits. The hybrid convergence criterion is more generic and accurate. However, because it often iterates more, it may be computationally more expensive for some problems.

NAME: IPUN
DESCRIPTION: Uniform pressure adjustment for compressible flows (if :envvar:`IPUN` = 0, there is no adjustment; if :envvar:`IPUN` = 1 adjust the pressure once at the end of each cycle).

NAME: ICOUPLE
DESCRIPTION: Flag to control coupling between neighboring Fluid Structure Interaction (FSI) components :envvar:`m` and :envvar:`m1` (see :envvar:`IFSI(m)` above). Default is no coupling between components (i.e., a fixed boundary condition). Note that the coupling is always symmetric: the coupling of component :envvar:`m` to :envvar:`m1` is always the same as :envvar:`m1` to :envvar:`m`. If coupling is doubly defined between two components, the higher-valued :envvar:`ICOUPLE` prevails.

NAME: CONTPV
DESCRIPTION: Quantity to be contoured under the vectors (cannot be used with :envvar:`CLRTPV`)

NAME: CLRTPV
DESCRIPTION: If specified, this quantity is used to color the vectors in both 2-D and 3-D vector plots. The color used for each vector is determined by the value of this quantity at the vector location. The quantities that can be specified are the same as those for :envvar:`CONTPV(n)`. (Cannot be used with :envvar:`CONTPV`.)

NAME: IDATPV
DESCRIPTION: Data source flag for vector plots

NAME: IPERV
DESCRIPTION: Indicator for type of plot

NAME: IV3OPT
DESCRIPTION: 3-D vector option

NAME: IVTYP
DESCRIPTION: Vector plot type

NAME: IVVEW
DESCRIPTION: Viewpoint for 3-D perspective velocity vector plot :envvar:`n`

NAME: NVPLTS
DESCRIPTION: Number of velocity vector plots

NAME: VELMX
DESCRIPTION: Scaling multiplier for velocity vectors

NAME: VMAX
DESCRIPTION: If specified as a positive value, :envvar:`VMAX(n)` is the maximum velocity for scaling vector lengths for all plots generated for vector plot :envvar:`n` (all plots would use the same vector length scale making comparison between plots easier). However, if :envvar:`VMAX(n)` is a negative value, all plot n vector plots would use the same vector length scale, determined by the maximum velocity in the accumulated data.

NAME: VQMN
DESCRIPTION: If specified, :envvar:`VQMN(n)` is the minimum contour or coloring value for all plots generated for vector plot :envvar:`n`. If :envvar:`VQMN(n)` is not specified, the minimum value for each plot will be the minimum data value for that individual plot.

NAME: VQMX
DESCRIPTION: If specified, :envvar:`VQMX(n)` is the maximum contour or coloring value for all plots generated for vector plot :envvar:`n`. If :envvar:`VQMX(n)` is not specified, the maximum value for each plot will be the maximum data value for that individual plot.

NAME: VSCALE
DESCRIPTION: Scaling multiplier for velocity vectors

NAME: IPERV
DESCRIPTION: Indicator for type of plot

DESCRIPTION: Indicates if serial fall back  is on or off (DEPRECATED). If an input file from

NAME: MPIMMEMU

NAME: MPIPARADIGM

NAME: IACDEP

NAME: IF_PBLOCK_ENABLED
DESCRIPTION: Activation flag for initial particle block :envvar:`n`

NAME: NPXYZ
DESCRIPTION: Total number of initial particle blocks

NAME: NBLK_TOTAL
DESCRIPTION: Total number of particles generated in initial particle block :envvar:`n`. :envvar:`NBLK_TOTAL(n)` is used for directions for which extents have been specified by :envvar:`XPL(n)`, :envvar:`XPR(n)`, :envvar:`YPF(n)`, :envvar:`YPBK(n)`, :envvar:`ZPB(n)` and :envvar:`ZPT(n)`, but not the number of particles :envvar:`NPX(n)`, :envvar:`NPY(n)`, or :envvar:`NPZ(n)`, see below.

NAME: NPX
DESCRIPTION: Number of particles in x-direction in initial particle block :envvar:`n`

NAME: NPY
DESCRIPTION: Number of particles in y-direction in initial particle block :envvar:`n`

NAME: NPZ
DESCRIPTION: Number of particles in z-direction in initial particle block :envvar:`n`

NAME: IBLK_SET
DESCRIPTION: Particle generation flag at initial particle block :envvar:`n`

NAME: XPL
DESCRIPTION: Minimum x-coordinate of initial rectangular particle block :envvar:`n`

NAME: XPR
DESCRIPTION: Maximum x-coordinate of initial rectangular particle block :envvar:`n`

NAME: YPBK
DESCRIPTION: Maximum y-coordinate of initial rectangular particle block :envvar:`n`

NAME: YPF
DESCRIPTION: Minimum y-coordinate of initial rectangular particle block :envvar:`n`

NAME: ZPB
DESCRIPTION: Minimum z-coordinate of initial rectangular particle block :envvar:`n`

NAME: ZPT
DESCRIPTION: Maximum z-coordinate of initial rectangular particle block :envvar:`n`

NAME: UPI
DESCRIPTION: Initial particle x-direction velocity at initial particle block :envvar:`n`

NAME: VPI
DESCRIPTION: Initial particle y-direction velocity at initial particle block :envvar:`n`

NAME: WPI
DESCRIPTION: Initial particle z-direction velocity at initial particle block :envvar:`n`

NAME: IBLK_CLASS
DESCRIPTION: Particle class generated at initial particle block :envvar:`n`

NAME: BLK_SPECIES
DESCRIPTION: Concentration factor for species :envvar:`l` of class :envvar:`IBLK_CLASS(n)` at initial particle block :envvar:`n`. The scale is relative and is automatically normalized in the solver to sum up to 1.0.

NAME: BLK_TEMPERATURE
DIMENSIONS: Initial temperature of particles at initial particle block :envvar:`n`. Used when :envvar:`IF_BLK_TEMPERATURE(n)` = 0, :envvar:`IFENRG` = 2 or 3 and :envvar:`IBLK_CLASS(n)` points to a material particle class, for example, the mass particles.

NAME: IF_BLK_TEMPERATURE
DESCRIPTION: Flag for setting the initial temperature of particles at initial particle block :envvar:`n`. Used when :envvar:`IFENRG` = 2 or 3 and :envvar:`IBLK_CLASS(n)` points to a material particle class, for example, the mass particles.

NAME: BLK_PRESSURE
DESCRIPTION: Initial pressure of particles at initial particle block :envvar:`n`. Used when :envvar:`IBLK_CLASS(n)` = 16, i.e., generates gas particles.

NAME: IF_BLK_PRESSURE
DESCRIPTION: Flag for setting the initial pressure of particles at initial particle block :envvar:`n`. Used when :envvar:`IF_BLK_PRESSURE(n)` = 0 and :envvar:`IPBLK_CLASS(n)` = 16, i.e., generates gas particles.

NAME: BLK_CHARGE
DESCRIPTION: Electric charge of particles at initial particle block :envvar:`n`. Used when :envvar:`IECHRG` = 1 and :envvar:`IBLK_CLASS(n)` points to a material particle class, for example, the mass particles.

NAME: BLK_ATTRIBUTE
DESCRIPTION: Initial value of user-defined particle attribute :envvar:`m` at initial particle block :envvar:`n`. Used when a user-defined particle class is generated, :envvar:`IBLK_CLASS(n)` = 1 to :envvar:`NSC_PART`.

NAME: IF_PSOURCE_ENABLED
DESCRIPTION: Activation flag for particle source :envvar:`n`

NAME: IPPKT
DESCRIPTION: Number of particle sources

NAME: PARTICLESOURCENAME
DESCRIPTION: Particle source :envvar:`n` name (up to 256 characters)

NAME: RATET
DESCRIPTION: Time-dependent rate of particle creation at source :envvar:`n` at time :envvar:`TMS(t)`.

NAME: FRATET

NAME: IRATETC
DESCRIPTION: The column number for rate of particle creation at source :envvar:`n` in the external file

NAME: TMS
DESCRIPTION: Time table for time-dependent particle source parameters

NAME: UPP

NAME: VPP
DESCRIPTION: Particle initial y-direction velocity at particle source :envvar:`n`

NAME: WPP
DESCRIPTION: Particle initial z-direction velocity at particle source :envvar:`n`

NAME: XPPR
DESCRIPTION: Upper x-coordinate limit for volumetric particle :envvar:`n`

NAME: YPPF
DESCRIPTION: Lower y-coordinate limit for volumetric particle source :envvar:`n`. For a cylindrical mesh (:envvar:`ICYL` = 1 in MESH), :envvar:`YPPF` is in degrees.

NAME: YPPBK
DESCRIPTION: Upper y-coordinate limit for volumetric particle source :envvar:`n`. For a cylindrical mesh (:envvar:`ICYL` = 1 in MESH), :envvar:`YPPBK` is in degrees.

NAME: ZPPB
DESCRIPTION: Lower z-coordinate limit for volumetric particle source :envvar:`n`

NAME: ZPPT
DESCRIPTION: Upper z-coordinate limit for particle source :envvar:`n`

NAME: YPSOU0
DESCRIPTION: Initial y-coordinate of particle source reference point in space system.

NAME: ZPSOU0

NAME: VTPSOU

NAME: FVTPSOU

NAME: IOMYTPSOUC

NAME: FOMXTPSOU
DESCRIPTION: The external filename for tabular angular velocity component in x'-direction of body system for particle source :envvar:`m` as a function of time (used only if :envvar:`IOMXTPSOUC(m)` :math:`\geq` 2)

NAME: FOMYTPSOU
DESCRIPTION: The external filename for tabular angular velocity component in y'-direction of body system for particle source :envvar:`m` as a function of time (used only if :envvar:`IOMYTPSOUC(m)` :math:`\geq` 2)

NAME: FOMZTPSOU
DESCRIPTION: The external filename for tabular angular velocity component in z'-direction of body system for particle source :envvar:`m` as a function of time (used only if :envvar:`IOMZTPSOUC(m)` :math:`\geq` 2)

NAME: ISRC_SET
DESCRIPTION: Particle generation flag at particle source :envvar:`n`

NAME: ISRC_CLASS
DESCRIPTION: Particle class generated at particle source :envvar:`n`

NAME: SRC_SPECIES
DESCRIPTION: Concentration factor for species :envvar:`l` of class :envvar:`ISRC_CLASS(n)` at particle source :envvar:`n`. The scale is relative and is automatically normalized in the solver to sum up to 1.0.

NAME: SRC_TEMPERATURE
DIMENSIONS: Initial temperature of particles at particle source :envvar:`n`. Used when :envvar:`IF_SRC_TEMPERATURE(n)` = 0, :envvar:`IFENRG` = 2 or 3 and :envvar:`ISRC_CLASS(n)` points to a material particle class, for example, the mass particles.

NAME: IF_SRC_TEMPERATURE
DESCRIPTION: Flag for setting the initial temperature of particles at particle source :envvar:`n`. Used when :envvar:`IFENRG` = 2 or 3 and :envvar:`ISRC_CLASS(n)` points to a material particle class, for example, the mass particles.

NAME: SRC_PRESSURE
DESCRIPTION: Initial pressure of particles at particle source :envvar:`n`. Used when :envvar:`ISRC_CLASS(n)` = 16, i.e., generates gas particles.

NAME: IF_SRC_PRESSURE
DESCRIPTION: Flag for setting the initial pressure of particles at particle source :envvar:`n`. Used when :envvar:`IF_SRC_PRESSURE(n)` = 0 and :envvar:`IPSRC_CLASS(n)` = 16, i.e., generates gas particles.

NAME: SRC_CHARGE
DESCRIPTION: Electric charge of particles at particle source :envvar:`n`. Used when :envvar:`IECHRG` = 1 and :envvar:`ISRC_CLASS(n)` points to a material particle class, for example, the mass particles.

NAME: SRC_ATTRIBUTE
DESCRIPTION: Initial value of user-defined particle attribute :envvar:`m` at particle source :envvar:`n`. Used when a user-defined particle class is generated, :envvar:`ISRC_CLASS(n)` = 1 to :envvar:`NSC_PART`.

NAME: NPSOUR
DIMENSIONS: Particle source identifier for restarts; used to identify the old particle source number if particle sources have been changed for restart runs.

NAME: IF_PHIST_ENABLED
DESCRIPTION: Activation flag for history particle :envvar:`n`

NAME: PLOCTL
DESCRIPTION: Title for history particle :envvar:`n` (30 characters maximum)

NAME: ULOCP
DESCRIPTION: Initial u-velocity for history particle :envvar:`n`

NAME: VLOCP
DESCRIPTION: Initial v-velocity for history particle :envvar:`n`

NAME: WLOCP
DESCRIPTION: Initial w-velocity for history particle :envvar:`n`

NAME: XLOCP
DESCRIPTION: Initial x-coordinate for history particle :envvar:`n`

NAME: YLOCP
DESCRIPTION: Initial y-coordinate for history particle :envvar:`n`

NAME: ZLOCP
DESCRIPTION: Initial z-coordinate for history particle :envvar:`n`

NAME: IPROBE_CLASS
DESCRIPTION: Particle class represented by probe :envvar:`n`.  The properties of the probe are taken from those defined for particle species :envvar:`IPROBE_SPECIES(n)` of class :envvar:`IPROBE_CLASS(n)`.

NAME: IPROBE_SPECIES
DESCRIPTION: Particle species of class :envvar:`IPROBE_CLASS(n)` represented by probe :envvar:`n`. The properties of the probe are taken from those defined for particle species :envvar:`IPROBE_SPECIES(n)` of class :envvar:`IPROBE_CLASS(n)`.

NAME: PROBE_TEMPERATURE
DIMENSIONS: Initial temperature of probe :envvar:`n`. Used when :envvar:`IFENRG` = 2 or 3 and :envvar:`IPROBE_CLASS(n)` points to a material particle class, for example, the mass particles.

NAME: PROBE_CHARGE
DESCRIPTION: Initial electric charge of probe :envvar:`n`. Used when :envvar:`IECHRG` = 1 and :envvar:`IPROBE_CLASS(n)` points to a material particle class, for example, the mass particles.

NAME: PROBE_PRESSURE
DESCRIPTION: Initial pressure of probe :envvar:`n`. Used when :envvar:`IPROBE_CLASS(n)` = 16, i.e., points to the gas particle class.

NAME: PROBE_ATTRIBUTE
DESCRIPTION: Initial value of user-defined particle attribute :envvar:`m` of probe :envvar:`n`. Used when :envvar:`IPROBE_CLASS(n)` i.e., points to a user-defined particle class, :envvar:`IPROBE_CLASS(n)` = 1 to :envvar:`NSC_PART`.

NAME: IPROBE_RESTART
DESCRIPTION: Flag for history particle :envvar:`n` initialization during restarts, :envvar:`IFREST` = 1.

NAME: IAQSRP

DESCRIPTION: Direction of fluid released by source m (when flow rate is positive)

NAME: IFQSRP
DESCRIPTION: Index of fluid released by source m (when flow rate is positive)

NAME: IFSNKP
DESCRIPTION: Index of fluid removed by mass source :envvar:`m` (when flow rate is negative)

NAME: IVQSRP
DESCRIPTION: Indicator of volume or mass flow rate for source :envvar:`m`

NAME: MASSMOMENTUMNAME
DESCRIPTION: Mass/momentum source :envvar:`m` name (up to 256 characters)

NAME: NVNTS

NAME: NVTYP

NAME: ITQSRPC

NAME: YV

NAME: ZV

DESCRIPTION: Size of source :envvar:`m` along the x-direction. For spray bar source, :envvar:`NVTYP(m)` = 5, is the outer diameter of the spray bar.

NAME: YSIZE
DESCRIPTION: Size of a rectangular or elliptical source :envvar:`m` along the y-direction. For spray bar source, :envvar:`NVTYP(m)` = 5, is the length of the spray bar.

NAME: VNX
DESCRIPTION: Rotation around x-axis of source :envvar:`m`

NAME: VNY
DESCRIPTION: Rotation around y-axis of source :envvar:`m`

NAME: VNZ
DESCRIPTION: Rotation around z-axis of source :envvar:`m`

NAME: TMS
DESCRIPTION: Time table for time-dependent mass momentum source parameters

NAME: VV
DESCRIPTION: y-component of fluid velocity at source :envvar:`m` at time :envvar:`TMS(t)`

NAME: WV
DESCRIPTION: z-component of fluid velocity at source :envvar:`m` at time :envvar:`TMS(t)`

NAME: FVSOU

NAME: IVSOUC
